theorem
Th53: (for A being (Matrix of n,K) holds (A <> ( 0. (K,n) ) implies (ex B,C being (Matrix of n,K) st ((((B is  invertible & C is  invertible) & ( ( ( B * A ) * C ) * (1,1) ) = ( 1. K )) & (for i holds ((1 < i & i <= n) implies ( ( ( B * A ) * C ) * (i,1) ) = ( 0. K )))) & (for j holds ((1 < j & j <= n) implies ( ( ( B * A ) * C ) * (1,j) ) = ( 0. K )))))))
proof
let A being (Matrix of n,K);
assume A <> ( 0. (K,n) );
then consider i0 being (Element of ( NAT )),j0 being (Element of ( NAT )) such that A1: (1 <= i0 & i0 <= n) and A2: (1 <= j0 & j0 <= n) and A3: ( A * (i0,j0) ) <> ( 0. K ) by CKB59:1;
