then consider P being (Matrix of n,K),Q being (Matrix of n,K) such that A4: P is  invertible and A5: Q is  invertible and A6: ((( ( ( P * A3 ) * Q ) * (1,1) ) = ( 1. K ) & (for i holds ((1 < i & i <= n) implies ( ( ( P * A3 ) * Q ) * (i,1) ) = ( 0. K )))) & (for j holds ((1 < j & j <= n) implies ( ( ( P * A3 ) * Q ) * (1,j) ) = ( 0. K )))) by A1,A3,CKB47:1;
